<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 92 / International Company News: Gillette puts effort into male
toiletries
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
GILLETTE, the US toiletries and shaving products group, yesterday unveiled
its Gillette Series line as it prepares to foray into the male grooming
product arena.
Developed at a cost of about Dollars 75m, the 14 products that will form the
core of a line of shaving preparations, deodorants, anti-perspirants and
after-shave conditioners, will be the first toiletries to carry the Gillette
name.
The company will spend Dollars 125m to market the products in the North
Atlantic market and it has applied for more than 20 patents to cover new
technologies used, including a novel gel-based deodorant which will be
rolled out through a grid applicator.
Although Gillette has a chequered track record in toiletries, the company
has a strong presence in the men's shaving market. It expects the Dollars
6bn male grooming market to grow to nearly Dollars 12bn by the end of the
century.
The move is the latest effort by Gillette to expand from its established
product base. In the summer it launched a Sensor razor for women and
acquired a majority stake in the biggest razor blade maker in China. Earlier
this month it bought Parker Pen for Pounds 285m (Dollars 564m).
</TEXT>
