FT  23 SEP 92 / Labour calls for review of banking regulations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE LABOUR party yesterday called for a thorough review of banking
regulations once the results of the inquiries into last year's collapse of
Bank of Credit and Commerce International are published, Alison Smith
writes.
A 600-page US Senate report on the BCCI affair is due to be published today
and is expected to be sharply critical of the role of the Bank of England.
A report by Lord Bingham into whether BCCI was supervised properly by the
Bank and the government is now likely to be published in the week beginning
October 19, when parliament reassembles for normal sittings.
