</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OCCIDENTAL, the oil company that owned the ill-fated Piper Alpha platform,
is suing 26 contractor companies and at least one survivor after paying out
millions of pounds in compensation after the deaths of 167 men in the
disaster.
