<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 92 / Ownership of CD players up
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OWNERSHIP OF consumer durables has continued to rise in spite of the
recession, according to preliminary results from the 1991 General Household
Survey.
The biggest year-on-year rise was for compact disc players - 27 per cent of
British households owned one last year, up from 21 per cent in 1990. There
were also further surges in ownership levels for video recorders and
microwave ovens - 68 per cent owned a video (64 per cent in 1990) and 55 per
cent a microwave (50 per cent in 1990).
