<HEADLINE>
FT  23 SEP 92 / People: Sir Eric Pountain steps back from full-time role
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Eric Pountain is to become non-executive chairman of TARMAC at the end
of this year.
Until last year Sir Eric combined the role of chief executive and chairman,
but relinquished day-to-day running of the company when Neville Simms was
appointed chief executive.
This followed criticism of Sir Eric's stewardship of Britain's biggest
housebuilder during the late 1980s when the expansion of its UK
housebuilding operations left it exposed to the collapse of house prices and
sales.
Yesterday Sir Eric said that the appointment of Neville Simms had worked out
very well for both of them, but 'I have found lately that there is not
enough for me to do on a full-time basis. I also intend to accept other
non-executive directorships.'
Sir Eric's career moves mirror those of Sir Clifford Chetwood, the former
chief executive and chairman of WIMPEY who, in November 1990, stood down as
chief executive in favour of Joe Dwyer who, like Simms, is battling to
reduce group debt through a programme of disposals and tighter control over
spending.
The question is whether these are the final acts of both men. Sir Eric is 60
next year - the normal retirement age for Tarmac executives. Recently, there
has been speculation over Sir Clifford's role as non-executive chairman of
Wimpey following the appointment of Sir John Quinton, chairman of Barclays
Bank, as a non-executive director.
*****
Keith Egerton, md of TAYLOR WOODROW Property Company, has been appointed
chairman following the resignation of Peter Hedges.
*****
Philip Brown has been appointed group company secretary of HARRISON &amp;
CROSFIELD.
*****
Graham Wilson, managing director of United Newspapers and chairman of its
Extel Financial subsidiary, has resigned from the board of Extel Group,
which retains a small preferential share listing - a hangover from United's
1987 bid for Extel. Charles Stern, United Newspapers' new finance director,
replaces Wilson on the board of Extel Group, a non-trading company.
*****
Sheila Forbes, formerly group personnel director of Storehouse, has been
appointed director of human resources at REED INTERNATIONAL.
