FT  22 SEP 92 / International Company News: Circle K rises to Dollars 8.2m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CIRCLE K, the Arizona-based convenience store chain which has been operating
under Chapter 11 bankruptcy protection since 1990, yesterday turned in
first-quarter operating profits of Dollars 8.2m, compared with Dollars 6.4m
a year earlier.
The company, which has agreed to be acquired for about Dollars 402m by an
investor group, CK Acquisitions, led by Bahrain-based Investcorp, said it
expected to file an amended reorganisation plan by the end of this month.
The company suffered a net loss of Dollars 2.7m, or 10 cents a share, in the
quarter, reflecting the costs associated with its reorganisation.
A year earlier, Circle K recorded a net loss of Dollars 500,000, or 5 cents
a share.
Mr Bart Brown, chairman, said: 'Given the costs and complications associated
with the Chapter 11 process, we are pleased with these first-quarter
results.'
