<TEXT>
Sweden's central bank yesterday cut its overnight lending rate to the banks
to 50 per cent from 500 per cent, in an attempt to calm the markets, writes
Robert Taylor in Stockholm. The move came before trading started.
But doubts and confusion emerged over the exact details of the all-party
budget cuts package announced in outline on Sunday evening.
After considerable fluctuations the Stockholm bourse closed down 1.5 per
cent with a SKr380m (Pounds 36.9m) turnover. The fall was particularly
pronounced in the finance sector with a drop of 4 per cent.
