The move is part of a number of proposed board changes to be announced by
the end of the month.
Mr Hanson, aged 31, who is currently an associate director, joined the group
in 1990 from NM Rothschild, the investment bank which advises Hanson.
He is expected to be appointed to the board along with Mr Graham Dransfield,
aged 40, Hanson's senior solicitor, who joined the group in 1982.
Mr Alan Hagdrup, aged 59, a director since 1974, is expected to step down
from the board.
One of Hanson's advisers yesterday confirmed the board changes.
