the group and not just by his father.'
If appointed, Mr Hanson will be by far the youngest director.
Mr John Raos, aged 42, who is chief operating officer of Hanson Industries,
the US arm of Hanson, is the youngest member of the board.
The board appointments still have to be ratified by the non-executive
members.
They are not expected to oppose the moves.
The appointments will then go to shareholders for ratification.
Mr Hanson has been part of the conglomerate's acquisition team reporting to
the vice-chairmen, Mr Martin Taylor and Mr Derek Rosling.
