FT  22 SEP 92 / Observer: Suitable case
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Passing the office of a consistently late lunching colleague, a City broker
saw the nameplate on the door had been covered with a paper strip reading
NATO.
On inquiring, he was told the letters stood for:
'Needs alcohol to operate'.
