<HEADLINE>
FT  22 SEP 92 / UK Company News: Enron thwarted in North Sea gas move
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Enron, one of the largest US gas companies, has been thwarted in its attempt
to buy a block of North Sea gas production from Chevron.
The co-venturers - British Gas, Phillips Petroleum and Agip - have exercised
their pre-emption rights. The operating agreement allows them to pre-empt
for the same cash value as any offer received by Chevron.
British Gas said that the purchase was not intended to keep a competitor out
of the market but was made to secure further gas supplies. Terms of the deal
were not disclosed.
</TEXT>
