<HEADLINE>
FT  22 SEP 92 / Crisis in the UK Economy: IoD chief demands cut in interest
rates
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE LEADER of the Institute of Directors, yesterday called on the government
to cut interest rates to 8 per cent in the aftermath of the French
referendum.
Mr Peter Morgan, IoD director general, also called on the prime minister not
to ratify the Maastricht treaty. He said implementation in the present form
would be 'the height of folly' because of dissatisfaction in France and
elsewhere. The treaty was designed by 'other people' with other interests
and there was never anything in it for Britain.
The European exchange rate mechanism had been exposed as a 'multilateral
shambles' which had destroyed many businesses, added Mr Morgan.
