FT  22 SEP 92 / Plea on statutory audits
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE STATUTORY audit of all limited-liability companies should remain
compulsory, the Chartered Association of Certified Accountants said
yesterday in a submission to the Department of Trade and Industry.
It says that although reform may be required, abolition of the statutory
audit is not the solution and the audit is important for the Inland Revenue,
creditors and bankers.
The document follows growing pressure from other bodies for abolition of
audits for small companies.
The DTI said earlier this year that it might consider abolishing the
requirement for companies with turnovers below the VAT threshold of Pounds
36,600.
Industry and a number of professional bodies have argued that the audit is
costly and inefficient.
